<TITLE> New ICT law to introduce digital signatures </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 16 (bdnews24.com)The newly approved Information and Communication Technology (Amendment) Act 2009, if passed by parliament, will introduce digital signatures to Bangladesh. The cabinet approved the new ICT law on Thursday aiming at development of the sector, greater computer and Internet security and the curbing of tech crime. "The new law will allow appointment of a controller responsible for monitoring different developments in information technology," said Md Nazmul Huda, secretary to the science and ICT ministry. The amended act will serve to secure and protect online identities, online banking transactions and online payment services by introducing digital signatures. A top official in the ministry told bdnews24 that the new amendment to the act has removed legal barriers to the appointment of a controller. The controller's office will play a vital role in maintaining secure communication and information transfer. It will also accelerate communication between the government and international bodies. bdnew
